                <note rend="inline" type="source">693.119/421: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-04-15T18:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 15, 1919, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your April 10, 3 p.m.</p>
                <p>Does arms agreement contemplate the inclusion of Dalny as a Chinese port to which
                    consignment of arms and ammunition; other than sporting arms and ammunition in
                    small lots is to be prohibited. The Department believes Dalny should be so
                    included and you should consult with your colleagues with that end in view.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
